                "text": "When running Apache Tomcat with HTTP PUTs enabled it was possible to upload a JSP file to the server via a specially crafted request. This JSP could then be requested and any code it contained would be executed by the server."
              },
              "help": {
                "markdown": "When running Apache Tomcat with HTTP PUTs enabled it was possible to upload a JSP file to the server via a specially crafted request. This JSP could then be requested and any code it contained would be executed by the server.",
                "text": "When running Apache Tomcat with HTTP PUTs enabled it was possible to upload a JSP file to the server via a specially crafted request. This JSP could then be requested and any code it contained would be executed by the server."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1035.html",
